Citigroup’s Ugandan Unit Posts 4.4% Increase in Annual Profit

-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 
2011-04-28T05:46:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/citigroup-s-ugandan-unit-posts-4-4-increase-in-annual-profit.html
Citigroup Inc. (C) ’s Ugandan unit
posted a 4.4 percent increase in full-year income as deposits
and loans grew.  Net income climbed to 26.3 billion Ugandan shillings ($11
million) in 2010, from 25.2 billion shillings a year earlier,
Citibank Uganda Ltd. said in a statement published in the
Kampala-based  Daily Monitor  newspaper today. Loans and advances
more than doubled to 187.3 billion shillings, as deposits
climbed 38 percent to 403.2 billion shillings, it said.  Net interest income, the difference between what a bank
pays out for deposits and earns for loans, rose 11 percent to 29
billion shillings, the bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala via Nairobi at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 